<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,813,201,341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="147">Note. This species has an epigynum much modified, but the remaining morphological characters are very similar to those of the group in which the type species is located. Its inclusion in the genus may be corroborated with the future description of the male.</paragraph>
